Disgruntled workers are planning to block the road to Eskom's Mpumalanga offices this morning. The workers, who work for an Eskom subcontracter, have been sleeping outside one of the power stations for days. eNCA's Nqobile Madlala is covering the story for us. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Disgruntled workers are planning to block the road to Eskom's Mpumalanga offices on Monday morning. READ: Khato Civils workers want their money The workers, who work for an Eskom subcontractor, have been sleeping outside one of the power stations for days. They claim they were promised permanent jobs, something that has not happened.